<h2>How do you adjust the target temperature?</h2>
<p class="subtitle">Two interaction models — pick what feels right for a touchscreen</p>

<div class="cards">

  <!-- Option A: Drag knob -->
  <div class="card" data-choice="drag" onclick="toggleSelect(this)">
    <div class="card-image" style="background:#1a1a2e;padding:24px;display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;justify-content:center;min-height:220px;gap:8px;">
      <div style="position:relative;width:160px;height:160px;">
        <svg width="160" height="160" viewBox="0 0 160 160">
          <circle cx="80" cy="80" r="60" fill="none" stroke="#ffffff12" stroke-width="14" stroke-dasharray="350 28" stroke-dashoffset="-14" stroke-linecap="round"/>
          <circle cx="80" cy="80" r="60" fill="none" stroke="#f59e0b" stroke-width="14" stroke-dasharray="210 168" stroke-dashoffset="-14" stroke-linecap="round"/>
          <!-- knob with drag indicator -->
          <circle cx="80" cy="20" r="11" fill="#f59e0b" transform="rotate(216 80 80)" style="filter:drop-shadow(0 0 6px #f59e0b88)"/>
          <circle cx="80" cy="20" r="5" fill="#1a1a2e" transform="rotate(216 80 80)"/>
          <!-- arrows to suggest drag -->
          <text x="80" y="83" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#ffffff50" font-family="system-ui">drag knob</text>
        </svg>
        <div style="position:absolute;inset:0;display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;justify-content:center;color:#fff;gap:2px;">
          <span style="font-size:10px;opacity:.4;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:14px;">current</span>
          <span style="font-size:36px;font-weight:700;line-height:1">71°</span>
          <span style="font-size:13px;color:#f59e0b;margin-top:2px;">→ 72°</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div style="font-size:11px;color:#ffffff40;letter-spacing:.05em;">Living Room · Heat</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
      <h3>Drag Knob</h3>
      <p>Circular drag gesture to set target. Satisfying and precise. Requires pointer event handling — harder to implement cleanly on touch.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Option B: +/− buttons on the ring -->
  <div class="card" data-choice="buttons" onclick="toggleSelect(this)">
    <div class="card-image" style="background:#1a1a2e;padding:24px;display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;justify-content:center;min-height:220px;gap:8px;">
      <div style="position:relative;width:160px;height:160px;">
        <svg width="160" height="160" viewBox="0 0 160 160">
          <circle cx="80" cy="80" r="60" fill="none" stroke="#ffffff12" stroke-width="14" stroke-dasharray="350 28" stroke-dashoffset="-14" stroke-linecap="round"/>
          <circle cx="80" cy="80" r="60" fill="none" stroke="#f59e0b" stroke-width="14" stroke-dasharray="210 168" stroke-dashoffset="-14" stroke-linecap="round"/>
        </svg>
        <div style="position:absolute;inset:0;display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;justify-content:center;color:#fff;gap:2px;">
          <span style="font-size:10px;opacity:.4;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;">current</span>
          <span style="font-size:36px;font-weight:700;line-height:1">71°</span>
          <span style="font-size:13px;color:#f59e0b;margin-top:2px;">→ 72°</span>
        </div>
        <!-- − button at bottom-left of ring -->
        <div style="position:absolute;bottom:4px;left:4px;width:36px;height:36px;border-radius:50%;background:#ffffff15;backdrop-filter:blur(4px);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-size:20px;color:#fff;font-weight:300;">−</div>
        <!-- + button at bottom-right of ring -->
        <div style="position:absolute;bottom:4px;right:4px;width:36px;height:36px;border-radius:50%;background:#f59e0b;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-size:20px;color:#000;font-weight:700;">+</div>
      </div>
      <div style="font-size:11px;color:#ffffff40;letter-spacing:.05em;">Living Room · Heat</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
      <h3>+/− Buttons on Ring</h3>
      <p>Large tap targets at the bottom corners of the dial. Simple, reliable, fat-finger friendly. Same behavior as current card, new visual.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

</div>
